page.title: 15WIVELISCOMBE WOOD
page.content: Wiveliscombe wood is fifty acres,the wood consists of pine,oak and beech trees.The land around is mainly covered by ferns,grass,bluebells and moss.The two ponds are in different areas.One of them is near the house and the other one is on the otherside of the wood.The house was built in the 1930's.There are two balconies one at the front and one at the back.There are about twenty rooms and two staircases.There are six outhouses near the house.The sheds around the house are empty.At the back of the house the lawn used to be full of ferns and trees.There are sheds which have got tractors inside.The little sheds have got geese and chickens in them.In the woods you can often see deer.There is a small cottage in which the worker lives with his wife.
